    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n5742" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λέβης</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ητος</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">kettle, caldron</span>, for warming water
          or for boiling food over fire, <i><span class="en">Il.
            21.362</span></i>; in the Odyssey usually, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">basin,
            wash-basin</span>, held under the hands or feet while water was
          poured from a pitcher over them, <i><span class="en">Od.
            19.386</span></i>; called <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀνθεμόεις</span>,
          from the decoration, <i><span class="en">Od. 3.440</span></i>.
            
        </div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
